Program: Free Thinking
Title: The Real Game of Thrones: Power in 15th-Century England
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03f8c54
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 29 Aug 2014
A 15th-century English monarch was appointed by God and had absolute supremacy but how was that belief shaken when medieval kings were unfit to rule or the throne was contested? New Generation Thinker Sarah Peverley, from Liverpool University, looks at the way the people viewed their rulers during the Wars of the Roses. Producer: Fiona McLean First broadcast in October 2013. Show less